  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study will examine the prevalence of venous thromboembolism in children with acute
      lymphoblastic leukaemia treated in accordance with NOPHO ALL-2008. The investigators will
      prospectively study clinical symptomatic thromboses, asymptomatic central line-associated
      thromboses, and infections.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
